      "Microstructure_Info": {
        "Microstructure_Text": {
          "original": "FCC+L12 dual-phase structure. Average grain size reduced to 9.2 μm due to discontinuous precipitation (DP) of L12 phase. Mixed CP (continuous precipitation) and DP regions observed. In DP region: lamellar L12 nanorods enriched in Ni, Al, Ti but depleted in Co and Cr; cellular structures indiscernible; grain boundary migration observed. In CP region: cellular structures retained; FCC+L12 dual-phase. Highly coherent L12/FCC interface with small lattice mismatch (δ=0.28%). Partial dislocation annihilation indicated by reduced KAM value (0.67°). STEM-HAADF and APT confirmed: L12 phase enriched in Ni (52.8 at.%), Al (10.4 at.%), Ti (11.7 at.%) and depleted in Co (21.4 at.%), Cr (3.6 at.%); FCC matrix enriched in Co (49.0 at.%) and Cr (31.3 at.%).",
          "simplified": "FCC+L12 dual-phase; grain refinement to 9.2 μm from DP; lamellar L12 nanorods enriched in Ni/Al/Ti, depleted in Co/Cr; coherent interfaces; ~37 vol% L12"
        },
